.\" claudii manual — auto-synced to wiki via GitHub Actions
.TH CLAUDII 1 "April 3, 2026" "claudii 0.18.5" "claudii manual"
.
.SH NAME
claudii \- Fast Claude Code aliases with live model status and session insights
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claudii
.IR command " [" args ]
.PP
When invoked with no arguments,
.B claudii
shows a contextual summary: active session data, a rate-limit warning
(when 5h usage >= 80%), or a welcome message when no cache exists.
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Quick start — enable everything at once:
.B claudii on
.TP
Live health check:
.B claudii status
.TP
Show active sessions with cost and rate limits:
.B claudii se
.TP
Read a config value:
.B claudii config get aliases.cl.model
.TP
Switch CC-Statusline to dense layout:
.B claudii cc-statusline preset focused
.TP
Toggle only ClaudeStatus RPROMPT:
.B claudii claudestatus off
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claudii
is a zsh plugin and CLI for Claude Code power users:
fast aliases to launch Claude with the right model and effort,
live model health in your RPROMPT, and a metrics statusline inside Claude Code sessions.
.
.SH INSTALL
.B Homebrew (recommended):
.PP
.RS
.nf
brew tap bmmmm/tap
brew install claudii
.fi
.RE
.PP
Add to
.IR ~/.zshrc :
.RS
.nf
source "$(brew --prefix)/opt/claudii/libexec/claudii.plugin.zsh"
.fi
.RE
.PP
.B Manual:
.PP
.RS
.nf
git clone https://github.com/bmmmm/claudii ~/claudii
bash ~/claudii/install.sh
.fi
.RE
.
.SH LAUNCHING CLAUDE
Shell functions for fast model access.
Configured under the
.B aliases.*
config namespace.
Auto-fallback to a healthy model when the configured model is down
.RB ( fallback.enabled ).
.TP
.B cl
Claude Sonnet, high effort. General-purpose default.
.TP
.B clo
Claude Opus, high effort. Complex tasks, server work.
.TP
.B clm
Claude Opus, max effort. Maximum reasoning.
.TP
.B clq
Claude Sonnet, medium effort.
Launches in
.I search.dir
(default:
.IR ~/claude-search ).
Equivalent to
.BR "claudii search" .
.TP
.B clh
Show the alias table and run a live model health check.
.TP
.B clorch / cle
Example agent aliases — see
.BR "claudii agents" .
.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output structured JSON instead of formatted text.
Available for:
.BR status ", " sessions ", " cost ", " trends ", " doctor ", " version ", " agents .
.TP
.B \-\-tsv
Output tab-separated values (header + data rows).
Available for:
.BR sessions ", " cost .
.PP
When stdout is not a terminal, ANSI colors are stripped and plain text is emitted.
.B version
prints only the bare version number when piped.
.
.SH DISPLAY LAYERS
Three separate layers each serve a different scope:
.TP
.B ClaudeStatus (RPROMPT)
Model health indicators in the right-hand shell prompt.
Reads a local cache — no network calls in
.IR precmd .
Indicators:
.B \(dg
= ok,
.B \(ti
= degraded,
.B \(da
= down,
.B ?
= unreachable,
.B \(lB\(el\(rB
= loading,
.B \(rn
= refreshing.
.TP
.B Session Dashboard (above prompt)
Per-session summary lines above the prompt, rendered via the precmd hook.
Shows model, context %, cost, 5h rate limit + countdown.
Only shown after
.B claudii
commands; suppressed after
.BR se / si / sessions .
.TP
.B CC-Statusline (inside Claude Code)
Metrics line inside Claude Code sessions via the
.B statusLine
hook in
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Receives live JSON from Claude Code on each turn.
Segments configured via
.B statusline.lines
(see
.BR CONFIGURATION ).
.PP
Data flow:
.RS
.nf
Claude Code \(-> CC-Statusline (stdin JSON) \(-> cache \(-> Session Dashboard
                                            \(-> history-YYYY-MM.tsv
.fi
.RE
.
.SH COMMANDS
.
.SS Display Layer Control
.TP
.B on
Enable all three layers at once (ClaudeStatus, Session Dashboard, CC-Statusline).
.TP
.B off
Disable all three layers at once.
.TP
.BR "claudestatus " [on|off]
Toggle only the ClaudeStatus RPROMPT.
Without argument: show current state.
.TP
.BR "session-dashboard " [on|off]
Toggle only the Session Dashboard above the prompt.
Without argument: show current state.
Deprecated alias:
.BR dashboard .
.TP
.BR "cc-statusline " [on|off]
Toggle only the CC-Statusline inside Claude Code.
Modifies
.IR ~/.claude/settings.json .
Without argument: show current state.
.TP
.BI "cc-statusline preset " [name]
Switch the CC-Statusline layout to a named preset.
Without a name, lists available presets.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B focused
\(em dense 3-line layout: identity / metrics / env.
.IP \(bu 2
.B calm
\(em bare 2-line layout: model / context-bar.
.IP \(bu 2
.B default
\(em restore the shipped 5-line layout.
.RE
.IP
After switching, restart Claude Code to see the change.
Writes
.B statusline.lines
to
.IR config.json .
.TP
.BR "insomnii " [on|off|auto|status|install]
Manage the optional
.BR cc-insomnii (1)
bedtime clock segment.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.B on
\(em require delegation; doctor warns if the binary is missing.
.IP \(bu 2
.B off
\(em suppress delegation; the clock segment is empty.
.IP \(bu 2
.B auto
\(em delegate when installed, skip when not (default).
.IP \(bu 2
.B status
(or no argument) \(em show binary path and active mode.
.IP \(bu 2
.B install
\(em clone
.B $CC_INSOMNII_REPO
(default
.IR https://github.com/bmmmm/cc-insomnii )
and run its
.BR install.sh .
Idempotent.
.RE
.TP
.B explain
Component overview with current status, data flow, and symbol legend.
Aliases:
.BR layers ", " components .
.
.SS Model Health (ClaudeStatus)
.TP
.B status
Live model health check (bypasses cache).
Per-model status table with icons, last-check time, and active incidents.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Alias:
.BR s .
.TP
.BR "status " 5m|15m|30m|60m
Set the background cache refresh interval (default: 15m).
Values below 30s are rejected.
.
.SS Sessions and Cost
.TP
.B sessions
List active and recent sessions: model, context %, cost, rate limits,
worktree, agent context, and a fingerprint of top-5 files accessed.
Background sessions
.RB ( "claude --bg" )
are marked
.BR [bg] .
Supports
.BR \-\-json " and " \-\-tsv .
Aliases:
.BR se ", " ss .
.TP
.BI "sessions \-\-resume " id
Resume a session by ID.
Equivalent to
.BR "claude --resume " id .
.TP
.B sessions-inactive
Inactive (ended or stale) sessions with age, context, and rate-limit data.
Shows badges: pinned, stale, or idle.
Alias:
.BR si .
.TP
.BI "pin " session-id
Protect an inactive session from garbage collection.
Matches by session ID substring (first match wins).
.TP
.BI "unpin " session-id
Remove GC protection from a pinned session.
.TP
.B gc
Remove stale session cache files.
Pinned sessions are never removed.
Run
.B claudii si
to inspect before garbage collecting.
Alias:
.BR g .
.TP
.BI "resume " session-id
Resume a session by ID
.RB ( "claude --resume " id ).
Use
.B claudii se
to list IDs.
.TP
.B cost
Costs per period (today, week, month, year, all-time), with per-model breakdown.
Falls back to session cache files when no history exists yet.
Supports
.BR \-\-json " and " \-\-tsv .
Alias:
.BR c .
.TP
.B trends
Rolling 7-day cost chart, 30-day model split, costliest day, and spend trend.
Reads from
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history-YYYY-MM.tsv
(written by the CC-Statusline handler).
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Alias:
.BR t .
.TP
.B cache
Prompt-cache hit rate per day and per model (default: 7-day window).
Aggregated from JSONL transcripts under
.IR ~/.claude/projects .
First run is slower (5\(en30 s) while the cache warms; subsequent runs
only re-aggregate changed sessions.
.RS
.TP
.BI "\-\-days " N
Override the rolling window.
.RE
.
.SS Configuration
.TP
.B config
Show all config values.
.TP
.BI "config get " key
Read a value using dot-notation.
Example:
.BR "claudii config get aliases.cl.model" .
.TP
.BI "config set " "key value"
Set a value.
Example:
.BR "claudii config set statusline.models opus,sonnet" .
.TP
.B "config reset"
Reset all config to defaults.
.TP
.BI "config export " "[file]"
Print config as JSON, or write to
.I file
if specified.
.TP
.BI "config import " file
Replace config with a JSON file (backs up existing config first).
.TP
.B "config theme"
List available color themes. Active theme marked with an asterisk.
.TP
.BI "config theme " name
Set the active theme.
Available:
.B default
(magenta accent, standard ANSI) and
.B pastel
(softer 256-color palette).
Stored as
.B theme.name
in
.IR config.json .
.TP
.B agents
List configured agents (alias \(-> skill mapping) or show onboarding instructions.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Configure via:
.RS
.nf
claudii config set agents.clorch.skill orchestrate
claudii config set agents.clorch.model opus
claudii config set agents.clorch.effort high
.fi
.RE
.
.SS Local LLM (omlx / gateii)
.TP
.B "omlx status"
Show whether the omlx segment is wired in, the
.I active.json
path, and oMLX server reachability.
.TP
.B "omlx connect"
Detect a gateii install, store the path, and probe the server.
.TP
.B "omlx test"
Render the cc-statusline against a synthetic
.I active.json
with the omlx segment.
.TP
.B "omlx disconnect"
Remove the
.B omlx
entry from any custom
.B statusline.lines
layout.
.PP
Override the
.I active.json
path via
.B CLAUDII_OMLX_ACTIVE
or config key
.BR statusline.omlx_active_path .
.
.SS VPN State (vpnii)
Shows the active WireGuard tunnel name in the cc-statusline and RPROMPT.
State file:
.IR ~/.cache/claudii/vpnii .
.B claudii vpnii
wraps write/clear with privilege drop so the file is always user-owned.
.PP
Recommended wg-quick config:
.PP
.RS
.EX
[Interface]
\&...
PostUp  = claudii vpnii set HomeLab
PreDown = claudii vpnii clear
.EE
.RE
.TP
.BI "vpnii set " "<name>"
Mark tunnel
.I name
as active.
Resolves the target user via
.B SUDO_USER
\(rA console owner \(rA
.B $USER
\(rA
.BR CLAUDII_USER .
.TP
.B "vpnii clear"
Remove the state file.
Aliases:
.BR "vpnii down" ", " "vpnii off" .
.TP
.B "vpnii show"
Print the current tunnel name, or
.I "no tunnel"
when none is set.
Alias:
.BR "vpnii status" .
.PP
Tailscale is detected separately via interface scan
(IPv4 in 100.64.0.0/10) and needs no state file.
.
.SS Activity Heatmap (vibemap)
Opt-in prompt-timing tracker, rendered as an ASCII heatmap.
Default
.BR off .
When enabled, the cc-statusline appends one TSV line per render to
.IR ~/.cache/claudii/vibemap.tsv .
Schema:
.BR "epoch \\\\t weekday \\\\t hour \\\\t minute \\\\t model \\\\t sid8 \\\\t delta_ms" .
No prompt content is recorded.
.TP
.B vibemap
Weekday \[mu] 3-hour-bin grid (default view).
.TP
.BI "vibemap strip" " [--days N]"
Last
.I N
days \[mu] 24-hour strip (default 14, range 1\(en90).
.TP
.B "vibemap status"
Show enabled state, file path, entry count, and oldest entry.
.TP
.B "vibemap path"
Print the vibemap file path.
.TP
.B "vibemap clear"
Remove the vibemap file.
.PP
Enable:
.BR "claudii config set vibemap.enabled true" .
.
.SS System
.TP
.BI "search " "['query']"
Launch Claude Code in the configured search directory
.RI ( search.dir ,
default:
.IR ~/claude-search ).
If a
.I query
is provided it is passed as the initial prompt.
.TP
.B restart
Reload the plugin by sourcing
.IR ~/.zshrc .
.TP
.B update
Update claudii.
Auto-detects Homebrew (runs
.BR "brew upgrade claudii" )
or git
.RB ( "git pull --ff-only" ).
Run
.B claudii restart
after updating.
.TP
.B version
Print version. When piped, prints the bare number only.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
.TP
.B changelog
Release notes for the current version.
Alias:
.BR about .
.TP
.B doctor
Installation health check: Claude Code, jq, CC-Statusline config, cache directory,
completions, plugin load, cc-insomnii state, and version.
Supports
.BR \-\-json .
Alias:
.BR d .
.
.SH SHORTCUTS
.PP
.TS
l l.
s	status
se	sessions
ss	sessions
si	sessions-inactive
c	cost
t	trends
d	doctor
g	gc
about	changelog
.TE
.
.SH CC-STATUSLINE SEGMENTS
Each segment is separated by a dim
.B \(bv
character and omitted when its data is absent.
The layout is controlled by
.B statusline.lines
(array of arrays; each inner array is one output line).
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Segment	Example	Description
_
model	\fBClaude Sonnet 4.5\fR	Model name (bold); effort appended when != high; \[u25B2] when thinking active
context-bar	\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2588]\[u2591]\[u2591]\[u2591]\[u2591]\[u2591] 62% \[u26A1]73%	10-block bar + usable% + cache hit ratio
rate-5h	5h:17% \[u21BA]249m	5h rate limit + reset countdown (Pro/Max plans only)
rate-7d	7d:50% \[u21BA]3d15h	7d rate limit + reset countdown
cost	$0.42	Session cost in USD (cyan); omitted when zero
tokens	42.1K\(ua 8.3K\(da	Input / output tokens with K/M suffixes
lines-changed	+823 \-201	Git lines added (green) / removed (red); session total
duration	1h 23m	Wall-clock session duration (dim)
api-duration	api:45m	Time waiting for Claude API responses (dim)
burn-eta	ETA:180m	Estimated time until 5h limit exhausted (dim; requires >= 3 min session)
delta-5h	\[u03B4]5h:+12%	5h rate change since session start
delta-7d	\[u03B4]7d:+3%	7d rate change since session start
cache-create	\[u270E]1.2K	Tokens written into prompt cache this session
session-name	my-feature	Custom session name (from /rename or --name)
worktree	feat/login \[u23B7] main	Worktree + branch (dim)
dir	\[u2302] my-app	Working directory basename (dim)
github	\[u25C6] bmmmm/claudii #42	GitHub repo + active PR number (Claude Code 2.1.145+)
agent	@orc	Agent name prefixed @ (dim)
ruler	\(em\(em\(em\(em	Horizontal rule filling remaining terminal width
claude-status	Opus \[u2713]  Sonnet \[u2713]  Haiku \[u2713]	Model health from ClaudeStatus cache
clock	\[u263E] 23:30 +30m	Local time + bedtime nudge; delegates to \fBcc-insomnii\fR(1) when installed
.TE
.PP
.B context-bar color thresholds:
green < 70%, yellow 70\(en89%, red >= 90% (of usable context).
A dim
.B 1M
indicator is appended when the context window >= 1,000,000 tokens.
Cache hit ratio
.B \[u26A1]XX%
is shown when cache-read tokens are present (green >= 60%, yellow < 30%).
.PP
.B rate-5h / rate-7d:
color is cyan < 50%, yellow 50\(en79%, red >= 80%.
Set
.B statusline.rate_display
to
.B remaining
to flip percentages from "used" to "what's left"
(e.g.\&
.B 5h:62%
becomes
.BR 5h:38% ).
Color thresholds always key off the underlying usage.
.PP
.B clock:
when
.B cc-insomnii
is on
.B PATH
and
.B statusline.insomnii
is
.B auto
(default) or
.BR on ,
claudii pipes the upstream JSON to cc-insomnii and uses its output verbatim.
Set
.B statusline.insomnii
to
.B off
to suppress.
Bedtime forwarded as
.B CC_INSOMNII_BEDTIME
from
.B statusline.bedtime
(default
.IR 23:00 ).
.
.SH CONFIGURATION
User config:
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
(or
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/claudii/config.json
if set).
Created automatically from defaults on first run.
.PP
Key paths (dot-notation):
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Key	Default	Description
_
aliases.cl.model	sonnet	Model for \fBcl\fR
aliases.cl.effort	high	Effort for \fBcl\fR
aliases.clo.model	opus	Model for \fBclo\fR
aliases.clm.effort	max	Effort for \fBclm\fR
aliases.clq.model	sonnet	Model for \fBclq\fR / search
fallback.enabled	true	Auto-fallback on outage
fallback.opus.model	sonnet	Fallback when opus is down
status.cache_ttl	300	Status cache TTL in seconds
statusline.enabled	true	ClaudeStatus in RPROMPT
statusline.models	opus,sonnet,haiku	Models to monitor
statusline.lines	(5-line default)	CC-Statusline layout — array of segment-ID arrays
statusline.rate_display	used	Rate display: \fBused\fR or \fBremaining\fR
statusline.bedtime	23:00	Bedtime threshold (HH:MM, forwarded to cc-insomnii)
statusline.insomnii	auto	cc-insomnii delegation: \fBauto\fR/on/off
session-dashboard.enabled	off	Session Dashboard above prompt: on/off
search.dir	~/claude-search	Directory for search mode
ui.spinner	random	Spinner style (random/beam/wave/dots/pulse/bounce/arc/orbit/ascii)
debug.level	off	Log level: off/error/warn/info/debug
vibemap.enabled	false	Opt-in activity tracking
.TE
.
.SH STATUS CACHE
.I "${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii/status-models"
(override:
.BR CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR ).
Contains one line per model:
.PP
.RS
.nf
opus=ok
sonnet=down
haiku=ok
.fi
.RE
.PP
Refreshed automatically in the background when older than
.B status.cache_ttl
seconds.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CLAUDII_HOME
Path to the plugin directory. Set automatically.
.TP
.B CLAUDII_CACHE_DIR
Override the cache directory (default:
.IR ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/claudii ).
.TP
.B CLAUDII_LOG_LEVEL
Override the debug log level (off, error, warn, info, debug).
.TP
.B CLAUDII_SPINNER_MODE
Override the spinner animation (takes precedence over
.BR ui.spinner ).
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Overrides the config directory (default:
.IR ~/.config ).
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Overrides the base cache directory (default:
.IR ~/.cache ).
.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/claudii/config.json
User configuration.
.TP
.I $CLAUDII_HOME/config/defaults.json
Shipped defaults (read-only reference).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/status-models
Per-model status cache written by
.BR claudii-status .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/session-*
Per-session cache files written by the CC-Statusline handler
(model, context %, cost, rate-limit data).
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/history-YYYY-MM.tsv
Persistent session history (Flight Recorder), rotated monthly.
One TSV line per CC-Statusline update: timestamp, model, cost, context %,
5h rate, session_id, input_tok, output_tok, api_duration_ms.
Read by
.BR "claudii trends" " and " "claudii cost" .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/claudii/vibemap.tsv
Opt-in activity log (written only when
.B vibemap.enabled
is true).
.TP
.I ~/.claude/settings.json
Claude Code settings, modified by
.BR "claudii cc-statusline" .
.
.SH VISUAL LANGUAGE
.PP
.TS
l l l.
Symbol	Meaning	Color
_
\(bu	active session	green
\(ci	ended / inactive	dim
\(tf	warning	yellow
\(mu	error / failure	red
\(OK	ok / success	green
\(da	down (model)	red
~	degraded	yellow
|	separator	\(em
\[u2588]	progress bar filled	context-sensitive
\[u2591]	progress bar empty	dim
.TE
.PP
Internal:
.B _claudii_sym
.RI ( lib/visual.sh )
accepts names
.RB ( active ", " inactive ", " warn ", " error ", " ok ", " down ", " degraded ", " sep )
and prints the colored symbol.
Constants:
.B CLAUDII_SYM_*
(symbols),
.B CLAUDII_CLR_*
(ANSI colors).
.
